From qualitative analysis of 36 patient interviews and 16 caregiver interviews within
these communities, we derive themes related to benefits of portals, barriers to use,
concerns and desired features. Based on our initial findings, we present a set of
considerations for designing the patient portal user experience, aimed at helping
healthcare clinics to meet U.S. federally-mandated `meaningful use' requirements.},
